This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a new method for object tracking using convolutional neural networks. The paper also mentions the use of deformable convolution layers, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new method for enhancing feature representations using a gated fusion scheme. The paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as object tracking is a common task in robotics. Finally, the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with visual tracking of objects.
